            <p>Yesterday an Engineering buddy and best friend shared a picture on facebook. It was a picture of robot we build and won several robot competition with it.</p>
            <p>It was a simple analog robot built using six motors (six. Ikr but it had reasons) and affixed on thick wooden board with wheels. Here&rsquo;s the picture</p>
            <p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/jeYO595.jpg" alt="My First Robot" width="720" height="540" /></p>
            <!--breakhere-->
            <p>And it got to me, like I would never recall what was going through my mind at that time. Whatever I did, my friend did got lost into Mumbai Vapours along with that picture. All we have are couple certificates, a broken outdated robot and a facebook post.</p>
            <p>
                That knowledge lost forever. I never shared with anybody. Not that world missed out some thing big or anything but I lost an opportunity to teach my subordinates, my younger brothers who look upto me when it comes to computer science or engineering in general. <br /><br />But then again, I didn&rsquo;t had to create blog for that. I have been writing facebook notes for years now and I could have just used that facebook notes. Facebook notes are improved substantially over last couple years. I could have created blog using blogpost or wordpress or medium or tumblur : and I would have been just fine. <br /><br />All of above options makes sense because they were easier to setup. But they had plethora of drawbacks : <br /><br />I could not have any customized things like my favorite little game below.<br />

