                <br />Those websites are slow. With things I write , I am bound to have many HD images. If I made blog previously mentioned way, it would take million year to load a web page. Look at this webpage <span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #008080;"><a style="color: #008080; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2015/08/04/comcast-upgrades-its-internet-essentials-plan/31091247/">http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2015/08/04/comcast-upgrades-its-internet-essentials-plan/31091247/</a></span>So slow. I wanted to avoid things like this using services like cloudinary and faster servers so I can load images faster on mobile by customizing dimensions of images based on client.
            </p>
            <p><strong><strong><br /><br /></strong></strong></p>
            <p>I wanted to remove all things which are bad for SEO. I used google pagespeed tool while developing this site pretty proud to get 100/100 score. Also I am HTML5 Nazi. I hate when websites push things on clients while not adhering to HTML5 validation rules laid out by W3C. <br /><br />I wanted to format web page the way I want. <br />If my blog takes off, I wanted to be proud of it. I didn&rsquo;t wanted any regrets.</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
